      "solution": "✅ **Correct Answer: (C) Isaac Newton**\n\n📚 **NCERT Mapping:** Class 11 Physics | Chapter 8 — Gravitation | Topic: Newton's Universal Law of Gravitation\n\n⭐ **Exam Relevance: Very High** — This is a foundational GK+Science question. Every competitive exam from Class 10 level upward includes this. Pure recall — must-know for DRDO CEPTAM STAB.\n\n---\n\n**Sir Isaac Newton (1643–1727)** gave the **Universal Law of Gravitation** in 1687 in his landmark work **Philosophiæ Naturalis Principia Mathematica** (Mathematical Principles of Natural Philosophy).\n\n**Newton's Universal Law of Gravitation:**\n**F = G × (m₁ × m₂) / r²**\n\nWhere G = 6.674 × 10⁻¹¹ N·m²/kg² (Universal Gravitational Constant)\n\n---\n\n**(A) Charles Newton — INCORRECT:**\nThere is no famous scientist named 'Charles Newton'. This is a distractor option designed to confuse with the first name. Isaac Newton had no famous relative named Charles Newton in science.\n\n**(B) Charles Babbage (1791–1871) — INCORRECT:**\n**Charles Babbage** was a British mathematician and inventor known as the **'Father of the Computer'** — he designed the Difference Engine and Analytical Engine, forerunners of modern computers. He had nothing to do with the theory of gravity.\n\n**(C) Isaac Newton — CORRECT:**\n**Sir Isaac Newton** — English physicist, mathematician, and astronomer — formulated the law of universal gravitation, the three laws of motion, and invented calculus (independently of Leibniz). The famous story of the apple falling from a tree inspiring his gravitational thoughts is well-known, though its exact historical accuracy is debated.\n\n**(D) John Adams (1735–1826) — INCORRECT:**\n**John Adams** was the **2nd President of the United States**. He was a lawyer and politician, not a scientist. Completely unrelated to gravity theory.\n\n**Quick memory aid:** The two most important Newton facts:\n- **Isaac Newton** → Gravity, Laws of Motion, Calculus\n- **Charles Babbage** → Computer (Difference Engine)\n\n🔬 **DRDO Relevance:** Newton's law of gravitation is the basis for all satellite orbit calculations, missile trajectory planning, and ballistic computations in DRDO's weapons systems. Every DRDO missile trajectory engineer uses Newton's gravitational law daily."
