is mass-weight distinction is fundamental in DRDO's space systems — inertial guidance systems (INS) in missiles respond to mass (inertia), not weight. In a zero-g environment, a 1000 kg satellite still has all the inertia corresponding to 1000 kg (resists acceleration equally), even though it weighs nothing."
